    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Space Complexity Demonstration</title>\n    <style>\n        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 20px; }\n        #output { margin-top: 20px; }\n        .btn { margin: 5px; padding: 10px; background-color: #007BFF; color: white; border: none; cursor: pointer; }\n        .btn:hover { background-color: #0056b3; }\n        .complexity { margin-top: 10px; padding: 10px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border: 1px solid #ced4da; }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Space Complexity Demonstration</h1>\n<p>Space complexity measures the amount of working storage an algorithm needs. It considers both the temporary space allocated by the algorithm and the space required to hold input values.</p>\n\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"calculateSpace(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e'])\">Calculate Space for Array of Size 5</button>\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"calculateSpace(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h', 'i', 'j'])\">Calculate Space for Array of Size 10</button>\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"calculateSpace(['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f', 'g', 'h', 'i', 'j', 'k', 'l', 'm', 'n', 'o', 'p'])\">Calculate Space for Array of Size 16</button>\n\n<div id=\"output\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    function calculateSpace(array) {\n        // Space complexity in terms of the input size\n        const inputSize = array.length;\n        \n        // Let's say our algorithm also needs a few constant space variables\n        const constantSpace = 3; // e.g., a counter, a result variable, etc.\n        \n        // This is an O(n) space complexity algorithm\n        const spaceComplexity = `O(n) where n is the size of the array (${inputSize}).`;\n        \n        // Output the result\n        document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = `\n            <div class=\"complexity\">\n                Input Size: ${inputSize} elements<br>\n                Total Space Used: ${inputSize + constantSpace} (elements + constant)<br>\n                Space Complexity: ${spaceComplexity}\n            </div>\n        `;\n    }\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
